metadata.name: Mondrian Chess #9
metadata.description:
This artwork unifies the visual aesthetics of Mondrian with the mathematical beauty of chess. Each piece is a unique piece, as its representation is re-generated for every piece.

While the colors seems to be random placed in the grid, they are not an expose the inner working of the artwork.

metadata.name: River Prairie #41
Merkki #24
metadata.description:
Merkki is an exploration of primitive forms, randomness and bold lines.
Drawing inspiration from mid-70s iconic single-color logotypes, this project revolves heavily around constraints and minimalism.

- 5 different shape types
- 3 grid sizes
- Mostly monochrome, with occasional color accents

Press “s” to save a 4000x4000px image.

metadata.name: Missingno #130
metadata.description:
Containment has been breached and Missingno is on the loose. 
This unique beast doesn’t have a fixed shape and its appearance is ever-changing. 
Some call it a bug, very few know what it is truly made of.

Only now with present technology we managed to capture a fraction of its unlimited possible faces. 

Mint for a unique picture of Missingno, yet outdated the very moment it’s taken.


(Open live and click on the image to export)

metadata.name: Transmigration #28
metadata.description:
Generative visual composition, hybrid techniques, interactive, textures source created with GAN, assist by AI, eclectic, colors, transform in autonomous system, glitch, made with code, and modular patch.

* Interactive feature :
- place your mouse to visual screen,
- left click to glitch it or see other variations, and
- right click for reset or back to original composition.
